---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Terms of Service — GeoScore">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-10">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium bg-brand-500/10 text-brand-400 border border-brand-500/20 mb-4">
        Legal
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-3">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400">Last updated: 2026-07-21</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card p-8 space-y-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p>
          By using GeoScore, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the tool.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">2. Service Description</h2>
        <p>
          GeoScore is a free audit tool that scores websites 0-100 across 12 dimensions of AI search visibility (Generative Engine Optimization). The tool runs entirely in your browser; we do not operate any application servers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">3. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>You agree NOT to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>Use GeoScore to audit sites you don't own or have explicit permission to audit at high volume (rate-limit: 1 audit per 5 seconds per IP)</li>
          <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer, decompile, or otherwise extract source code for commercial resale (the source is already MIT-licensed and available on GitHub)</li>
          <li>Use automated scripts to scrape audit results for commercial purposes without permission</li>
          <li>Interfere with the operation of the service, the proxy servers, or any third-party services we rely on</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">4. Audit Results Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          GeoScore provides a <strong>best-effort heuristic score</strong> based on publicly observable signals. The score is educational and directional; it does not guarantee ranking or citation in any AI search engine. AI search algorithms change frequently and the tool may not reflect the latest signals.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          No specific outcome (crawling, indexing, ranking, citation) is guaranteed. Use the tool's recommendations as a starting point, not as definitive truth.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">5. No Warranty</h2>
        <p>
          The service is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the service will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, GeoScore and its contributors shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or indirectly, or any loss of data, use, or goodwill.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          Source code: MIT License (see <a href="https://github.com/qq136692547-cmyk/geo-score/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-400 hover:underline">LICENSE</a>). Blog content and educational materials: CC BY-SA 4.0. You may copy, modify, and redistribute with attribution.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Use of GeoScore is also subject to the terms of the third-party services we rely on for hosting and CORS proxying:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>GitHub Pages Terms of Service</li>
          <li>Cloudflare Terms of Service</li>
          <li>Google Analytics Terms of Service</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">9. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms occasionally. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance. Material changes will be noted in the GitHub repository changelog.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-3">10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions or concerns: <a href="https://github.com/qq136692547-cmyk/geo-score/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-brand-400 hover:underline">github.com/qq136692547-cmyk/geo-score/issues</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
